{"id":"1110.2129","submitter":"Aram Saharian","authors":"E.R. Bezerra de Mello, A.A. Saharian","title":"Vacuum polarization induced by a cosmic string in anti-de Sitter\n  spacetime","comments":"19 pages, 3 figures, discussion and references added, accepted for\n  publication in J. Phys. A","journal-ref":"J. Phys. A: Math. Theor. 45 (2012) 115402","doi":"10.1088/1751-8113/45/11/115402","report-no":null,"categories":"hep-th astro-ph.CO gr-qc quant-ph","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  In this paper we investigate the vacuum expectation values (VEVs) of the\nfield squared and the energy-momentum tensor associated with a massive scalar\nquantum field induced by a generalized cosmic string in D-dimensional anti-de\nSitter (AdS) spacetime. In order to develop this analysis we evaluate the\ncorresponding Wightman function. As we shall observe, this function is\nexpressed as the sum of two terms: the first one corresponds to the Wightman\nfunction in pure AdS bulk and the second one is induced by the presence of the\nstring. The second contribution is finite at coincidence limit and is used to\nprovide closed expressions for the parts in the VEVs of the field squared and\nthe energy-momentum tensor induced by the presence of the string. Because the\nanalysis of vacuum polarizations effects in pure AdS spacetime have been\ndeveloped in the literature, here we are mainly interested in the investigation\nof string-induced effects. We show that the curvature of the background\nspacetime has an essential influence on the VEVs at distances larger than the\ncurvature radius. In particular, at large distances the decay of the\nstring-induced VEVs is power-law for both massless and massive fields. The\nstring-induced parts vanish on the AdS boundary and they dominate the pure AdS\npart for points near the AdS horizon.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 10 Oct 2011 18:17:46 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 2 Feb 2012 16:41:15 GMT"}],"update_date":"2012-03-01"}
