es is established by observing that noncommuting\nmeasurements in quantum physics are mutually exclusive and can therefore be\ntreated as different levels of one and the same factor.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 10 Oct 2011 16:41:33 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 14 Oct 2011 11:36:09 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 11 Nov 2011 20:58:12 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Fri, 13 Jan 2012 23:57:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2012-09-04"}
